<DocsLayout title="Kubernetes Deployment">
  <h1>Kubernetes Deployment</h1>

  <p>
    This guide explains how to deploy AI Stack to a Kubernetes cluster using
    standard manifests.
  </p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>A running Kubernetes cluster (EKS, GKE, AKS, or Minikube)</li>
    <li><code>kubectl</code> installed and configured</li>
    <li>Docker registry to push images (Docker Hub, ECR, GCR)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>1. Build and Push Images</h2>
  <p>First, build and push the backend and frontend images to your registry.</p>
  <pre
    class="bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto border border-slate-800"><code class="text-slate-300"># Backend
docker build -t your-registry/ai-stack-backend:latest ./apps/backend
docker push your-registry/ai-stack-backend:latest

# Frontend
docker build -t your-registry/ai-stack-frontend:latest ./apps/frontend
docker push your-registry/ai-stack-frontend:latest</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Secrets Management</h2>
  <p>Create a Kubernetes Secret for your sensitive environment variables.</p>
  <pre
    class="bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto border border-slate-800"><code class="text-slate-300"># secrets.yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
  name: ai-stack-secrets
type: Opaque
data:
  # Base64 encoded values
  OPENAI_API_KEY: c2stLi4u...
  DATABASE_URL: cG9zdGdyZXNxbDovLy4uLi4=</code></pre>

  <p>Apply it:</p>
  <pre
    class="bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto border border-slate-800"><code class="text-slate-300">kubectl apply -f secrets.yaml</code></pre>

  <h2>3. Deploy Backend</h2>
  <pre
    class="bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto border border-slate-800"><code class="text-slate-300"># backend-deployment.yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: backend
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: backend
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: backend
        image: your-registry/ai-stack-backend:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8000
        envFrom:
        - secretRef:
            name: ai-stack-secrets
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: "500m"
            memory: "512Mi"
          limits:
            cpu: "1000m"
            memory: "1Gi"</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Deploy Frontend</h2>
  <pre
    class="bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto border border-slate-800"><code class="text-slate-300"># frontend-deployment.yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: frontend
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: frontend
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: frontend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: frontend
        image: your-registry/ai-stack-frontend:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000
        env:
        - name: NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL
          value: "http://backend"</code></pre>

  <h2>5. Ingress (Optional)</h2>
  <p>
    Use NGINX Ingress Controller or your cloud provider's Load Balancer to
    expose the services.
  </p>
  <pre
    class="bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto border border-slate-800"><code class="text-slate-300">apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: ai-stack-ingress
spec:
  rules:
  - host: ai-stack.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /api
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: backend
            port:
              number: 80
      - path: /
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: frontend
            port:
              number: 80</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
